If there are specific hours of the day or day(s) within a week when you would like an event to follow a particular rule, you can set its activity on an automatic, weekly recurring schedule. This feature is specific to each individual event rule and you can make additional changes, such as changing severity/priority, based on time of day. `}</p>
    <p>{`The Recurring Event Rules functionality is part of our `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://support.pagerduty.com/v1/docs/event-intelligence"
      }}>{`Event Intelligence`}</a>{` product, which is purchased separately from the core PagerDuty platform.`}</p>
    <p>{`To set a recurring schedule for an event rule, go to `}<strong parentName="p">{`Configuration`}</strong>{` :fa-arrow-right: `}<strong parentName="p">{`Event Rules`}</strong>{`, select the :fa-cog: dropdown next to the rule and then click `}<strong parentName="p">{`Edit Rule`}</strong>{`. In the `}<strong parentName="p">{`When should this rule be active?`}</strong>{` section, select `}<strong parentName="p">{`On a recurring schedule`}</strong>{`, specify the hours and day(s) when you would like the rule to be active, and then click `}<strong parentName="p">{`Save`}</strong>{`.
